<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 5:32PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Bamberg
County through 615 PM EDT...
At 531 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bamberg, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bamberg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
